Pillar 2: Account-Based Marketing as a Revenue Strategy

Account-Based Marketing (ABM) has evolved from a marketing tactic into a core revenue strategy. In 2025, high-performing revenue teams are aligning sales and marketing around a shared list of target accounts, focusing resources where they matter most. ABM is especially effective for enterprise and mid-market B2B companies targeting high-value deals.

Successful ABM programs are built on deep account insights. This includes understanding organizational structure, pain points, technology stack, and decision-making dynamics. Personalized campaigns are then crafted to engage multiple stakeholders within the same account through coordinated email marketing, content, LinkedIn outreach, and appointment setting.

Intent Amplify® specializes in full-funnel ABM execution. From account selection and data enrichment to multi-touch engagement and sales enablement, ABM campaigns are designed to generate qualified meetings and accelerate revenue. For U.S.-based businesses competing in saturated markets, ABM provides a strategic advantage by increasing deal size and improving win rates.

